transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, I'm trying to find out why are you guys taking money out of my account?

Speaker 1: Yeah, most likely you have a refill set for your prescription. I can take a look into your account.

Speaker 2: No, I don't have your...

Speaker 1: What's your last name?

Speaker 2: Hardeman.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: No.

Speaker 1: I didn't say anything, you just said your last name after your zip code.

Speaker 2: Five, three, Troy.

Speaker 1: Got it. One second.

Speaker 2: Yes, this is based off your first order you made with us, sir.

Speaker 1: Did you get an opportunity to read the terms and conditions after placing your first order?

Speaker 2: I don't know.

Speaker 1: The zip doesn't... No, that was... No, that wasn't supposed to happen, so either return it or...

Speaker 2: Yeah, no, I was just asking you because, like, I just asked you a question if you were able to read something,

Speaker 1: but if you didn't read it, it's fine. I was just asking you that.

Speaker 2: But basically on that terms and condition, it just states that every order is a prescription-based order,

Speaker 1: meaning that they need a refill date to be activated and sent out.

Speaker 2: The doctor set up every month for you because you got 10 pills, but it looks like it's still at the pharmacy,

Speaker 1: so I could just cancel it out and issue a refund.

Speaker 2: Just keep in mind your prescription itself, though, if I were to cancel that,

Speaker 1: you wouldn't be able to access it anymore because the doctor would delete the visit.

Speaker 2: Instead, I could always just freeze it out if you want that.

Speaker 1: I had already told them it don't work, so I didn't want...

Speaker 2: No worries. So no problem, then. I'll just cancel it out for you.

Speaker 1: You're all set. Have a good one. You'll get the refund back in three to five business days.

Speaker 2: Excuse me?

Speaker 1: You'll get the refund back in three to five business days.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. Thank you.

Speaker 1: No problem. Bye-bye.
